    <title>Products of ideals of linear forms in quadric hypersurfaces</title>
    <summary>  Conca and Herzog proved that any product of ideals of linear forms in a
polynomial ring has a linear resolution. The goal of this paper is to establish
the same result for any quadric hypersurface. The main tool we develop and use
is a flexible version of Derksen and Sidman's approximation systems.
</summary>
